Bill of Materials
Roaddog Labs Ltd Bart i3 Rework
file released under Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International license.

Frame

2 x 24" x18" 1/4" melamine, black or white, two sides laminated

Rods

2 x M5-.8 x 300 mm threaded rod, Z axis lead screws

2 x M8 x 320 mm smooth rod, (320 mm will work also)

4 x M8 x 370 mm smooth rod 

Bearings

11 x LM8UU linear bearings
 3 x 624ZZ bearings


Printed Parts

3 x Y clips
1 x Y endstop bracket
1 x Y motor bracket

1 x X carriage
1 x x endstop block
1 x X end motor
1 x X end idler
1 x X idler

1 x extruder body 
1 x extruder idler
1 x hot end mounting clip
1 x fan duct

1 x z endstop bracket

Misc Hardware

1 x M7 hobbed drive gear, filament drive gear
2 x GT2 pulley, 20 teeth, 5 mm diameter mounting hole
2 meters GT2 belt

4 x rubber feet

2 x 3/16" ID poly tubing, 1" long each, coupler tubing 

1 x 214 x 200 borosilicate glass print bed

4 x small binder clips for glass bed

4 bed springs (get final specs)
2 extruder springs (get final specs)

Fasteners  (totals rounded up from final prototype, shcs count not exact)

40 x 6-32 square nut, frame
40 x 6-32 x 5/8" pan head machine screws, frame
4 x 6-32 x 1/2" pan head machine screws, frame
4 x #6 flat washer, frame

20 x  M3 x 10 mm shcs, motor mounts, endstop screws
25 x  M3 x 12 mm shcs, motor/Z endstop bracket mounting, feet mounting
05 x  M3 x 14 mm shcs,
05 x  M3 x 16 mm shcs,
08 x  M3 x 25 mm shcs,
06 x  M3 x 30 mm shcs, 
02 x  M3 x 35 mm shcs,
02 x  M3 x 50 mm shcs,

55 x  M3 washer
30 x  M3 hex nut
12 x  M3 nyloc nut

07 x  M4 x 20 shcs extruder mount, extruder idler
01 x  M4 x 30 shcs Y idler bearing

06 x  M4 hex nut
10 x  M4 flat washer
03 x  M4 nyloc nut

02 x  M5 nut




4 x nylon spacers (snap fit does not fit iduino/Arduino pcb mounting hole)

Electronics

1 x RAMPS with Arduino compatible board
5 x Stepstick A4988 drivers

1 x 40x40x10 12 volt axial fan

5 x NEMA 17 stepper motors, recommend 76 oz/in holding torque

1 x 350 watt, 12 volt PSU

1 x MK2A heated bed







